    {
      "id": "3229328297e6e03874614d981e73837597a1c028",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2013-09-11 04:01:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI wonder if there is any supportign data that this patch helps something?\n\nIn the end past testing indicated most of the overhead here comes from cpu cache ping-pong, and it would happen regardless of if it's a spinlock or rwlock, I suspect.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ee3eb54d700a4dc6864622247e17574e2fce959b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 142
      },
      "date": "2013-09-18 09:20:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nNo, it was not measured separately from other changes in the initial \"various optimizations\" patch. The main reason of the patch was that with 40-disk RAID-0 and obdfilter-survey test perf output showed some contention on that lock. Your reasoning looks correct - more complicated locking is needed to remove contention here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
